    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2963736649" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2963736649" />
    <a title="AAmell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17625403-aamell"><img alt="AAmell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1361306774p2/17625403.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2963736649?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="AAmell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="AAmell" href="/user/show/17625403-aamell">AAmell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780786942657" href="/book/show/222338.Streams_of_Silver">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2963736649" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11243020637644816038">A++<br/><br/>This book was absolute non-stop action from page 1. It&apos;s 377 pages but feels like 100 with how fast it reads. You&apos;ll be hard pressed to put this thing down at any point.<br/>Salvatore is a genius. Period. No wonder the Drizzt series is considered the pinnacle of Fantast story telling. I really want to read the LOTR books now to see how they stack up to Salvatore (but that&apos;s a discussion for another day).<br/><br/>Salvatore is incredible at setting up those kinds of situations that give you goosebumps- you k</span>
  <span id="freeText11243020637644816038" style="display:none">A++<br /><br />This book was absolute non-stop action from page 1. It's 377 pages but feels like 100 with how fast it reads. You'll be hard pressed to put this thing down at any point.<br />Salvatore is a genius. Period. No wonder the Drizzt series is considered the pinnacle of Fantast story telling. I really want to read the LOTR books now to see how they stack up to Salvatore (but that's a discussion for another day).<br /><br />Salvatore is incredible at setting up those kinds of situations that give you goosebumps- you know, the ones where shit has hit the fan, but something that has been building for a long time comes to life and saves the day. Typically, these events can be seen as forced, out of nowhere, and lame (Deus Ex Machina, if you will). But Salvatore sets everything up perfectly. I'm hard pressed to find any plot holes or faults in the character's thought processes in these types of moments. He's just able to somehow weave a story that fits together seamlessly. <br /><br />And that ending?! I mean, come on. Every story I've read thus far had had me saying "Well now I HAVE to read the next one," and this book is no different. I've already ordered the next book for pick up this week. And the next book is higher rated than this one? Are you kidding me? How can this possibly get any better than perfection?<br /><br />I can't stress how much of a genius storyteller Salvatore is. I wasn't at all into Fantasy until my buddy bought me Homeland (Drizzt's first book), and now I can't image having lived through my life without having read these books. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11243020637644816038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


