    <a title="James" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7677767-james"><img alt="James" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358501923p2/7677767.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/475781227?book_show_action=true">Dec 11, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James" href="/user/show/7677767-james">James</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer475781227&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer475781227" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4114789537310146147">Not as great as Icewind Dale #1, but that&apos;s OK.<br/><br/>Likes:<br/>- Wulfgar and his appetite (for not only adventure, but food as well/third helping of breakfast)<br/>- Regis and his ruby wokring on locals to get some ponies, and eventually having a meal (since he had only eaten one supper that day) and having to decline the fourth helping, haha!<br/>- Bruenor&apos;s warm side, as well as both Drizz&apos;t&apos;s and his pride in the young warrior Wulfgar.<br/>- The ivy mansion with some humorous elements (statue of actual wizard from an</span>
  <span id="freeText4114789537310146147" style="display:none">Not as great as Icewind Dale #1, but that's OK.<br /><br />Likes:<br />- Wulfgar and his appetite (for not only adventure, but food as well/third helping of breakfast)<br />- Regis and his ruby wokring on locals to get some ponies, and eventually having a meal (since he had only eaten one supper that day) and having to decline the fourth helping, haha!<br />- Bruenor's warm side, as well as both Drizz't's and his pride in the young warrior Wulfgar.<br />- The ivy mansion with some humorous elements (statue of actual wizard from an unsuccessful mix of potions and the family dog who was a second cousin, again a victim of bad potion mixture)<br /><br />Dislikes:<br />- Still has quite similar parts to the Lord of the Rings<br /><br />Overall, a good read but I liked #1 more... Still liking the adventure and can't wait for what's next though!<br /><br />* Passages:*<br />" There was a sense of urgency about him, like a spirited horse on a short rein. Fires hungry for adventure burned in his pale eyes as clearly as in Bruenor's, but unlike the dwarf, Wulfgar's gaze was not fixed upon the straight road before them. He was a young man out to view the wide world for the first time and he continually looked about, soaking up every sight and sensation that the landscape had to offer."<br /><br />Drizzt: "I said it clearly [...] take the axe and leave the ungrateful dwarf."<br />Wulfgar: "Twas the nose that confused me [...] more akin to an axe-head than to any nose I have ever seen!"<br />"Bruenor unconsciously looked down his long snout. 'Bah!' he growled, 'I'll find me a club!' and he tromped off into the forest."<br /></span>
