<div id="review_2102565630" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2102565630" />
    <a title="Jacob Moreno" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48547981-jacob-moreno"><img alt="Jacob Moreno" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2102565630?book_show_action=true">Aug 24, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jacob Moreno" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jacob Moreno" href="/user/show/48547981-jacob-moreno">Jacob Moreno</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2102565630" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14330521645943676272"> Streams Of Silver was yet another fantastic read in the Legend Of Drizzt series. The Author, R. A. Salvatore, has done a wonderful job throughout the series of keeping the reader interested and always wanting for more. In this book, however, It was more superbly done than all of the others before it. I am already in the middle of the next book The Halfling&apos;s Gem.<br/> As always we have our favorite dark elven stoic Drizzt Do&apos;Urden and friends, but this time they are put on an astounding quest. The q</span>
  <span id="freeText14330521645943676272" style="display:none"> Streams Of Silver was yet another fantastic read in the Legend Of Drizzt series. The Author, R. A. Salvatore, has done a wonderful job throughout the series of keeping the reader interested and always wanting for more. In this book, however, It was more superbly done than all of the others before it. I am already in the middle of the next book The Halfling's Gem.<br /> As always we have our favorite dark elven stoic Drizzt Do'Urden and friends, but this time they are put on an astounding quest. The quest is ravaged with danger at every corner. They find themselves in a heap of trouble time and time again and excitingly deal with everything the road ahead has to offer them. This is truly one of the more action packed books of the series. I personally loved all of the conflict and action packed events in this book. It just went from one exciting event to another and keeps the reader wonderfully interested in whats to come next.<br /> Throughout the story, we get an incredible look into Drizzt's inner turmoil in regards to his homeland and him being different from his kin. Facing questions of if he would ever be excepted for the person he is and not the race of his people as he has been ever since he first left their acquaintance. It is a sad and lonely life he lives that I think a lot of people can connect and empathize with.<br /> Overall the story is fantastic and dark and wonderfully written in ways that make the reader feel and emphasize with the characters and the path they walk. One can only hope that the next book is as equally amazing as this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14330521645943676272" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


